commit.message:
Fix PNG header and footer.

* The PNG header is wrong in a way that png files can be found, but carving
  produces output that needs repair before viewing.
* The PNG footer is just completely wrong.

Fix both by using the correct PNG signature as header and the full IEND
chunk as footer.

The return value of getopt is an int, not a char

This fixes the option parser on architectures with an unsigned 'char',
where scalpel previously just silently exited, as -1 becomes 255.
Small typo in comment

Merge pull request #6 from samcorbin/patch-1

Header is required while footer is optional.

Updated README, Fixed Build Permissions, tagged for release
Updated README, Fixed Build Permissions, tagged for release
removed configure script.  Run bootstrap first. Updated README
Formatting changes, conversion of tabs to spaces, consistent tab settings etc.
Formatting changes, conversion of tabs to spaces, consistent tab settings etc.

Fixed issue where CarveInfo structures were getting freed prematurely, resulting in crashes. The fix involves iterating over the carve list queues and only freeing the element on the queue if it was added as a STARTCARVE or STARTSTOPCARVE element. This is required to ensure that we only free the structures once.
Need to NULL terminate the argv array being passed to initializeState().
Added a note to scalpel_carveSingleInput() that it has been deprecated and should not be used.

Added new Scalpel library interface functions. libscalpel_initialize() opens the audit file, reads the configuration file, allocates storage and sets up the thread pool. libscalpel_carve_input() is called for each file to be carved. libscalpel_finalize() releases the resources that were set up in libscalpel_initialize.
The old library API function, scalpel_carveSingleInput() will be removed once applications that use it have been updated.

Removed code that attempted to kill threads as it does not work the same on all platforms. In particular, pthreads-win32 requires installation of a device driver in order for this functionality to work.

Incorporated Vico's fix for scalpel hanging. Basically, the reader thread now lets the main thread know that it is finished reading by placing a dummy buffer on the queue with bytesread = 0 and beginreadpos = 0.
Fixed a memory leak and added a hack to kill processing threads.
Fixed memory leak associated with the tokenarray in processSearchSpecLine and moved exception throwing after cleanup function calls.
Added freeing of the buf member to syncqueue_destroy()
Changed constness of base_name return value to keep gcc on Linux happy.
Moved free(info) out of the block that was checking to see if the input is a block device.
remove extra slash from base_name for Windows paths
removed dirname from Makefile.win
Initial commit to sleuthkit repo with license change and library design.
